burnAdminFromModuleRole(bytes32).details: The module itself can still grant and revoke it's own roles. This only burns third-party access to the role.

params.role: The role to remove admin access from

params.module: The address of the module to generate the hash for
params.role: The ID number of the role to generate the hash for

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive. Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point. WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

params.roleId: The role to be checked on.
params.token: The token to check the threshold for.

grantGlobalRole(bytes32,address).details: Only the addresses with the Owner role should be able to call this function

params.target: The address to grant the role to

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

params.role: The identifier of the role to grant
params.target: The address to which to grant the role.

params.role: The role to be made token-gated
params.threshold: The minimum balance of the token required to qualify for the role.
params.token: The token for which the threshold will be set.

hasModuleRole(bytes32,address).details: It will use the calling address to generate the role ID. Therefore, for checking on anything other than itself, hasRole() should be used

params.role: The identifier of the role we want to check
params.who: The address on which to perform the check.

identifier().details: The identifier is defined as the keccak256 hash of the module's      abi packed encoded major version, url and title.

init(address,(uint256,uint256,string,str.details: CAN be overriden by downstream contract.MUST call `__Module_init()`.

params.configData: Variable config data for specific module                   implementations.

makeRoleTokenGatedFromModule(bytes32).details: This function is only callable by an active Module for itself. Admin should use setTokenGated().Calling this function does not specify WHICH token to use for gating. That has to be done with 'grantTokenFromModule()'

params.role: The role to be made token-gated

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeGlobalRole(bytes32,address).details: Only the addresses with the Owner role should be able to call this function

params.target: The address to grant the role to

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

params.role: The identifier of the role to revoke
params.target: The address to revoke the role from.

setThreshold(bytes32,address,uint256).details: This function does not validate the threshold. It is technically possible to set a threshold above the total supply of the token.

params.roleId: The ID of the role to be modified
params.threshold: The user will need to have at least this number to qualify for the role.
params.token: The token for which to the threshold.

params.threshold: The new minimum balance of the token required to qualify for the role.
params.token: The token for which the threshold will be set.

setTokenGated(bytes32,bool).details: Admin access for rescue purposes. If the role has active members, they need to be reovked first.

params.role: The ID of the role to be modified
params.to: The new value to be set.

params.newAdmin: The new role to which to transfer admin access to
params.roleId: The role on which to peform the admin transfer

burnAdminFromModuleRole(bytes32).notice: Irreversibly burns the admin of a given role.

generateRoleId(address,bytes32).notice: Helper function to generate a bytes32 role hash for a module role

getManagerRole().notice: Returns the role ID of the manager role

getOwnerRole().notice: Returns the role ID of the owner role

getThresholdValue(bytes32,address).notice: Returns the threshold amount necessary to qualify for a given token role

grantGlobalRole(bytes32,address).notice: Grants a global role to a target

grantRoleFromModule(bytes32,address).notice: Used by a Module to grant a role to a user.

grantTokenRoleFromModule(bytes32,address.notice: One-step setup for Modules to create a token-gated role and set its threshold.

hasModuleRole(bytes32,address).notice: Asks whether an address holds the required module role to execute         the current transaction.

hasTokenRole(bytes32,address).notice: Checks if an account qualifies for a token-gated role.

makeRoleTokenGatedFromModule(bytes32).notice: Sets up a token-gated empty role.

revokeGlobalRole(bytes32,address).notice: Revokes a global role from a target

revokeRoleFromModule(bytes32,address).notice: Used by a Module to revoke a role from a user.

setThreshold(bytes32,address,uint256).notice: Sets the minimum threshold for a token-gated role.

setThresholdFromModule(bytes32,address,u.notice: Allows a Module to set the Threshold of one of it's roles

setTokenGated(bytes32,bool).notice: Sets if a role is token-gated or not.

transferAdminRole(bytes32,bytes32).notice: Transfer the admin rights to a given role.
